#https://docs.alliancecan.ca/wiki/Tutoriel_Apprentissage_machine/en

Tensorflow installation on Graham/Narval:
- module load python/3
- module load python/3.11.5

create a venv for tensorflow and activate:
- virtualenv --no-download tensorflow
- source tensorflow/bin/activate
- pip install --no-index --upgrade pip
- pip install numpy --no-index

- (check what version is available on CC)
- pip install --no-index tensorflow==2.16.1
- (or) pip install --no-index --find-links=/cvmfs/soft.computecanada.ca/custom/python/wheelhouse/gentoo2023/x86-64-v3 tensorflow==2.16.1

- pip install --no-index --find-links=/cvmfs/soft.computecanada.ca/custom/python/wheelhouse/gentoo2023/x86-64-v3 tensorflow-probability
- (or) pip install --upgrade tensorflow-probability

- pip install tf-keras 

other libraries as needed
- pip install keras, pandas, matplotlib, scipy
 (or)
- pip install --no-index numpy
- pip install --no-index matplotlib
